ody></table></figure></div><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><em>There Are Places In The World Where=
 Rules Are Less Important Than Kindness </em>is a collection of newspaper a=
rticles Rovelli wrote from 2010-2020 on physics and philosophy. Each is cha=
racteristically beautiful and thought-provoking. One was so timely it slapp=
ed me in the face.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><em>Newton the Alchemist</em>, origina=
lly published on March 19, 2017, deals with the seeming contradiction betwe=
en &#8220;the traditional image of him [Newton] as the father of science&#8=
221; and his lifelong pursuit of the now-discredited field of <strong>alche=
my</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Why would such a rational thinker &#8211; <e=
m>the</em> rational thinker &#8211; waste decades in pursuit of something s=
o frivolous and irrational?&nbsp;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px =
solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em>Was it a vain=
 hope in the first place? Was it a project that should have been discarded =
even before it began? </em></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em>On the contra=
ry: <strong>many of the key problems posed by alchemy, and quite a few of t=
he methods it developed, in particular with reference to the transformation=
 of one chemical substance into another, are precisely the problems that wo=
uld soon give rise to the new discipline of chemistry.</strong>&nbsp;</em><=
/p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em>Newton does not manage to take the critic=
al step between alchemy and chemistry. That would be down to scientists of =
the next generation, such as Lavoisier, to achieve.</em></p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1=
em 0;">Like a good bubble, alchemy&#8217;s promise of gold and immortality =
attracted a swarm of smart people, including Newton, to try to crack the co=
de. The exhaust of their failed attempt created a new, bigger, and much mor=
e important field of study.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Without alchemy, there is no =
chemistry (or, at least, chemistry doesn&#8217;t arrive as quickly). More g=
enerally, without experimentation and curiosity and adventures down ultimat=
ely fruitless rabbit holes, there is no progress.</p><div class=3D"captione=
