1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But alas, not e=
ven Sir Isaac Newton could turn shit into gold, not even after decades of w=
ork.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 1em 0;">Isaac Newton seems like an odd person to fail at alchemy.&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">Odd that he failed because we&#8217;re talking about the =
guy who discovered the three laws of motion, the theory of universal gravit=
y, that white light is a mixture of colors, and differential calculus.&nbsp=
; His tomb at Westminster Abbey reads, &#8220;&#8203;&#8203;Sibi gratulentu=
r Mortales, Tale tantumque exstitisse HUMANI GENERIS DECUS,&#8221; which tr=
anslates to &#8220;Mortals rejoice that there has existed such and so great=
 an ornament of the human race!&#8221; (Puja: take notes.)&nbsp;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;=
">Odd that such an ornament to the human race even tried because we&#8217;r=
e talking about <em>alchemy</em>, a debunked pseudo-science. As one <a href=
=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uhDAMhU8z2YFIwPwssuimV-gSmcQzRI=
