 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Retrying the same ideas in a =
frothier market and pumping harder with the same broken underlying mechanic=
s wasn&#8217;t a useful experiment. No new seed of the <em>real</em> valuab=
le idea was sowed in the process &#8211; no chemistry from this alchemy. Wo=
rse, regular people lost their life savings, and it seems as if a handful h=
ave taken their own lives as a result. That&#8217;s tragic and terrible and=
 the people responsible should be held accountable to the fullest extent po=
ssible.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But I&#8217;m worried that in crypto, and across =
the markets more generally, the sentiment &#8211; or vibe, as the kids woul=
d say &#8211; is in danger of shifting too far away from experimentation.&n=
bsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 1em 0;">That shows up in all of the proud crypto bears loudly proc=
laiming the whole thing was a scam all along and the fintwit pseudos rippin=
g Peloton and Shopify and Zoom and the other companies whose inventions mad=
e an awful pandemic a lot better for a lot of people.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"=
color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">I&#=
8217;d bet (Not Financial Advice&#8482;&#65039;) that Zoom, Peloton, and Sh=
opify are all worth more in five years than they are today, but even if the=
y go to zero, I don&#8217;t see the value in dunking on companies who&#8217=
;ve at the very least made work, fitness, and entrepreneurship more accessi=
ble and pushed those categories forward because the market overvalued them.=
&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;">We&#8217;re guilty of this on both sides: lionizing comp=
anies and their founders for high valuations, and ripping them to shreds wh=
en valuations fall.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">That&#8217;s the weirdest part of a b=
ear market: <strong>the people who are rooting for something other than oth=
er people to succeed and humanity to progress are the ones winning</strong>=
=2E If the long arc of market history is=20=
any indication, they won&#8217;t be =
winning for long, or over the long-term, but the environment that it create=
s in the interim feels super dark.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">(And yes, on the other side,=
 <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkU1PwzAMhn9Nc5zysXxwyAFpcA=
IJISEElyppvC2iTUfiMvbvcbcDUhTZcvy-9pMhIBzmevGnuSFbrx4vJ_AFzm0ERKhsaVD7nLww0=
im9vWPJb5Nw2rHc-n0FmEIePdYF2GmJYx4C5rlcOziXmh29jkPk3IjgQIELJBLBRB4SBBHUPt58=
w5IylAE8_EC9zAXYME8TFFyl2OiPiKfWqftOPtLBc16n29Abyj6hwBB6pShuGHBpFAgttdWWSy4=
st8Ypt-3UI0nsJO-kQQrM67F-n1-e9y-7j6eHX_X2_t6WM8tecim5FkZIbbTdqM3gpNQ6hWCCNH=
